16:30.006 --> 16:32.673
Oh, uh, yeah. I got a fade.

16:32.808 --> 16:35.943
Yeah, I was gonna say
that-that your hair is pink.

16:35.945 --> 16:37.744
(chuckles): Right?
So, let me get this straight.

16:37.780 --> 16:39.680
It's okay for your daughter

16:39.682 --> 16:42.767
to shave her head,
but it's not okay

16:42.769 --> 16:46.037
for my daughter to dress
a certain way? Is that...?

16:50.910 --> 16:54.912
Okay, I really don't know
what to say, so we... Duke...

16:54.981 --> 16:57.848
we're gonna go
to the classroom now.

16:59.068 --> 17:01.735
Bye, Riley.

17:01.804 --> 17:04.939
(groans) Jesus.

17:04.941 --> 17:06.807
What is wrong with people?

17:06.826 --> 17:07.942
Mom, stop.

17:08.077 --> 17:10.895
I mean, are you serious?
I have chills.

17:11.013 --> 17:13.814
-Calm down.
-Okay, fine, baby.

17:13.949 --> 17:16.700
You got it. I'll stop.

17:16.769 --> 17:18.969
-So fucking annoying.
-Oh, my God.

17:19.038 --> 17:20.905
♪ Looking back at all the... ♪

17:36.673 --> 17:39.607
(exhales):
Okay.

17:41.678 --> 17:43.878
Okay. "Clean, dry paper clip."

17:44.047 --> 17:47.748
Oh, Mom, we need paper clips.
We don't have any at our table.

17:47.883 --> 17:49.900
Copy that.

17:49.936 --> 17:51.902
I'll go get some.

17:58.844 --> 18:00.577
Oh. Hi. Excuse me.

18:00.613 --> 18:02.980
Yeah, those are ours,
so you can't just take them.

18:03.115 --> 18:05.666
I'm sorry.

18:05.801 --> 18:07.735
I thought it was okay.

18:07.737 --> 18:09.670
We're all doing
the same experiment.

18:09.772 --> 18:12.473
Okay, well, maybe you should
ask first, 'cause it's rude.

18:12.608 --> 18:14.608
You can't just go
and take people's things.

18:14.744 --> 18:16.810
-Okay.
-Okay.

18:16.879 --> 18:18.946
I'm just gonna go ahead
and take these now.

18:19.015 --> 18:21.765
It's kind of what I figured.
Mother of the year. Good job.

18:21.834 --> 18:24.668
-Cool. Thank you.
-Cool.

18:26.706 --> 18:29.506
Jesus, that guy is such a dick.

18:29.575 --> 18:30.908
-Mom. Mom, don't.
-(sighs)

18:31.043 --> 18:33.844
-Why can't anyone be a person?
-Give me the paper clips.

18:33.880 --> 18:37.448
Here. Got my head bit off
for those stupid things.

18:37.583 --> 18:39.467
-Mom, you're ruining it.
-Sorry.

18:41.003 --> 18:44.004
Okay. What's next?

18:48.878 --> 18:51.545
-(chuckles)
-I finished it.

18:51.614 --> 18:54.548
-It's okay. See?
Paper clip floated.
-Cool.

18:54.683 --> 18:56.666
-All right,
let's get out of here.
-Okay.

18:56.702 --> 18:57.868
But I'm gonna go
meet Pepper again

18:57.904 --> 18:59.603
before the next experiment.

18:59.639 --> 19:01.672
Do you have to?
There's only ten minutes left.

19:01.741 --> 19:02.873
Do you have to leave me?

19:02.959 --> 19:04.675
Mom, it's okay. Let me go.

19:04.810 --> 19:07.611
-Fine. Okay.
-I'll meet you at room 18.

19:07.647 --> 19:09.013
Just be there in ten minutes.

19:09.015 --> 19:10.848
-Got it.
-Okay.

19:12.968 --> 19:14.968
-Cool.
-Sorry about your dad.

19:15.004 --> 19:16.770
-Sorry about you.
-"Sorry about you"?

19:16.839 --> 19:19.506
-Should be sorry about you.
-Sorry about your face.

19:19.542 --> 19:20.908
I don't know
who she thinks she is.

19:20.910 --> 19:22.976
Oh, my God. Wasn't that
a fun field trip last week?

19:23.012 --> 19:25.645
We had the most awesome docent.

19:25.681 --> 19:27.648
She taught us what branches
and leaves we could eat,

19:27.783 --> 19:30.668
how to start a fire
and make soap.

19:30.670 --> 19:32.736
Mmm.

19:32.872 --> 19:34.738
Okay, come on.

19:34.774 --> 19:36.673
Salaam.

19:36.742 --> 19:38.542
-Ah!
-Salaam. (speaking Farsi)

19:38.611 --> 19:40.010
Salaam Sam Joon, how are you?

19:40.012 --> 19:42.012
I'm good. How are you guys?

19:42.014 --> 19:43.814
-How's Kayla?
-Ugh.

19:43.949 --> 19:46.900
Kayla is having so much trouble
with her teacher.

19:46.936 --> 19:48.836
The math? She is struggling.

19:48.905 --> 19:50.704
I don't like that teacher.

19:50.773 --> 19:53.574
-She's having so much problem
with her.
-Mmm.

19:53.709 --> 19:55.709
I have to go.
I have to get to that room.

19:55.845 --> 19:57.578
I made tahdig for the class.
(chuckles)

19:57.713 --> 19:59.579
Oh. (speaking Farsi)

19:59.615 --> 20:03.467
No fair. You guys have all
the Persian moms in your room.

20:03.602 --> 20:05.735
-Aw.
-I'll see you guys later.

20:05.771 --> 20:08.739
(all speaking Farsi)

20:08.741 --> 20:09.940
(Sam sighs)

20:09.942 --> 20:12.877
-Oh, hi.
-Hi.

20:16.949 --> 20:18.866
See you later.

20:26.742 --> 20:29.576
Duke. Duke.

20:29.579 --> 20:31.712
We're over here. Come on.

20:36.669 --> 20:38.735
Excuse me. Mrs. Fornges?

20:38.771 --> 20:40.671
Mrs. Fornges,
you got to move us.

20:40.740 --> 20:41.805
-Huh?
-Yeah.

20:41.941 --> 20:43.607
I can't across from that woman

20:43.676 --> 20:44.874
and her sociopathic son.

20:44.911 --> 20:47.944
-Please.
-Oh, okay. No problem.

20:47.980 --> 20:49.947
Thank you.

20:53.669 --> 20:55.835
Duke.

20:55.872 --> 20:57.838
No, over here, baby.
We're over here.

20:57.973 --> 20:59.573
This table now.

20:59.708 --> 21:01.909
Yeah.

21:01.978 --> 21:04.578
Hi.

21:04.647 --> 21:06.847
Mom, I can't believe you
right now.

21:06.849 --> 21:08.933
-You're so embarrassing.
Oh, my God.
-What?

21:09.068 --> 21:11.735
-(sighs)
-There were too many people
at that table.

21:11.870 --> 21:14.471
Mrs. Fornges did it.
I didn't do it.

21:14.540 --> 21:17.474
Mom, you said you'd be over it
if I got over it.

21:17.610 --> 21:18.675
That means you didn't mean it,

21:18.711 --> 21:19.877
and that means
you're a hypocrite.

21:20.012 --> 21:21.945
Okay, I'm sorry.

21:21.948 --> 21:24.481
I just want to do
the experiment with you

21:24.550 --> 21:26.767
and have fun without any drama,
okay, baby?

21:26.769 --> 21:27.768
Come on.

21:27.903 --> 21:30.570
Sit down. It's gonna be fun.

21:30.606 --> 21:32.572
Thank you.

21:32.608 --> 21:34.574
Oh.

21:34.610 --> 21:36.510
We're okay, right?

21:36.579 --> 21:39.847
Yeah. We're fine.

21:42.768 --> 21:45.669
So... anyway, maybe, uh,
we'll get a coffee

21:45.705 --> 21:48.038
at some point... together.

21:49.609 --> 21:50.858
You and me.

21:50.976 --> 21:52.910
DUKE:
Mom.

21:54.947 --> 21:58.899
Are you aware of the fact
that you owe me an apology

21:59.034 --> 22:00.767
and you're withholding it?

22:00.803 --> 22:02.036
Or did you forget?

22:03.706 --> 22:04.705
What's the matter with you?

22:04.774 --> 22:05.839
And with your son?

22:05.875 --> 22:07.641
What?

22:07.643 --> 22:08.642
Mom, come on.

22:09.712 --> 22:10.778
Do you know

22:10.913 --> 22:12.846
that you drove
onto a school parking lot

22:12.915 --> 22:14.848
on your cell phone
without barely looking up?

22:14.850 --> 22:16.867
Do you know how many kids
you almost hit?

22:16.869 --> 22:18.935
Get away from me.

22:18.971 --> 22:21.004
No. No.

22:21.007 --> 22:24.575
No. No.
I would like to step outside.

22:25.645 --> 22:27.744
-Step outside?
-Yes.

22:27.763 --> 22:30.547
I would like you and I
to step outside

22:30.683 --> 22:33.600
on the playground
so I can beat you up.

22:34.737 --> 22:36.770
Just like your psycho son did
to my daughter.

22:36.839 --> 22:38.539
(sighs)

22:40.843 --> 22:42.642
-Excuse me.
-Hmm.

22:42.712 --> 22:44.644
-Come on. Let's go. Come on.
-Hey. Hey!

22:44.780 --> 22:47.648
-Come on. I would like you
to go outside with me.
-Hey. Hey! Hey!

22:47.783 --> 22:49.533
-Hey!
-(grunts)

22:49.668 --> 22:51.000
-(gasps)
-(crying)

22:51.037 --> 22:52.569
SHAK'S MOM:
Shak?

22:56.642 --> 22:59.943
Okay, we're even. We're even.

22:59.979 --> 23:02.746
Come on, don't cry. Don't cry.

23:02.881 --> 23:04.715
Don't... cry.

